---
---
<section id="install" class="install"><div class="wrap">
  <p class="kicker">Install</p>
  <h2 class="serif">Bring Equipt into your assistant.</h2>
  <div class="tabs" role="tablist" aria-label="Install instructions">
    <button class="tab active" data-tab="web" role="tab" aria-selected="true" id="tab-web" aria-controls="panel-web">claude.ai / desktop</button>
    <button class="tab" data-tab="cc" role="tab" aria-selected="false" id="tab-cc" aria-controls="panel-cc">Claude Code</button>
    <button class="tab" data-tab="cli" role="tab" aria-selected="false" id="tab-cli" aria-controls="panel-cli">Equipt CLI</button>
    <button class="tab" data-tab="soon" role="tab" aria-selected="false" id="tab-soon" aria-controls="panel-soon">Cursor / Codex / Antigravity</button>
  </div>
  <div class="panel" data-panel="web" id="panel-web" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tab-web">
    <ol class="steps">
      <li>Grab a <b>plugin zip</b> — a whole category, e.g. <code>equipt-marketing.zip</code> — or a single <b>skill zip</b> from the latest <a href="https://github.com/Salah-XD/equipt/releases">Release</a>.</li>
      <li>In <b>claude.ai</b> / <b>desktop</b>: <b>Customize → Personal plugins (+) → Create plugin → Upload plugin</b> — or <b>Skills (+) → Create skill → Upload a skill</b> for just one.</li>
      <li>It’s live in your chats — no code, no setup.</li>
    </ol>
    <p class="soon">Plugins need a paid plan (Pro / Max / Team) and bundle their agents (active in Cowork &amp; Claude Code); single-skill uploads work on Free too. Power users can wire the whole marketplace into Claude Code — see the next tab.</p>
  </div>
  <pre class="panel" data-panel="cc" id="panel-cc" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tab-cc" hidden>/plugin marketplace add Salah-XD/equipt
/plugin install equipt-marketing</pre>
  <pre class="panel" data-panel="cli" id="panel-cli" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tab-cli" hidden>npx @equipt/cli init
npx @equipt/cli add equipt-marketing   # or a single skill: add cold-outreach-writer</pre>
  <div class="panel" data-panel="soon" id="panel-soon" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tab-soon" hidden>
    <p class="soon">Cursor, Codex, and Antigravity adapters are coming. The content is universal — the installers are in progress.</p>
  </div>
</div></section>
<style>
  .install { padding: 96px 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--hair); }
  .serif { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 34px); letter-spacing: .02em; margin: 8px 0 24px; }
  .tabs { display: flex; gap: 8px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .tab { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 13px; padding: 9px 14px; border: 1px solid var(--hair);
    border-radius: 8px; background: transparent; color: var(--muted); cursor: pointer;
    transition: color .18s ease, background-color .18s ease, border-color .18s ease; }
  .tab:hover { color: var(--ink); border-color: var(--accent); }
  .tab.active { color: var(--paper); background: var(--ink); border-color: var(--ink); }
  .tab.active:hover { color: var(--paper); }
  .panel { margin-top: 18px; background: var(--paper); border: 1px solid var(--hair); border-radius: 12px; padding: 20px;
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; }
  pre.panel { white-space: pre-wrap; }
  .panel a { color: var(--accent-text); }
  .soon { color: var(--muted); font-family: var(--font-body); }
  .panel .note { display: block; margin-top: 3px; color: var(--muted); font-size: 12.5px; }
  .panel code { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: .92em; }
  /* Install steps as a vertical roadmap — numbered nodes threaded on a rail. */
  .steps { list-style: none; margin: 4px 0 0; padding: 0; position: relative; counter-reset: step;
    font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 13.5px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--ink); }
  .steps li:not(:last-child)::after { content: ''; position: absolute; left: 12px; top: 24.5px; bottom: -1px; width: 2px;
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 24%, var(--hair)); }
  .steps li { position: relative; counter-increment: step; padding: 0 0 20px 40px; }
  .steps li:last-child { padding-bottom: 0; }
  .steps li::before { content: counter(step); position: absolute; left: 0; top: -1.5px; z-index: 1;
    width: 26px; height: 26px; border-radius: 50%; display: grid; place-items: center;
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 12px; color: var(--accent-text);
    background: var(--paper); border: 1px solid var(--hair); }
  .steps li:last-child::before { content: '✓'; color: var(--paper); background: var(--accent); border-color: var(--accent); }
  .steps b { font-weight: 600; }
  .steps a { color: var(--accent-text); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 2px; }
  .steps code { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: .92em; }
</style>
<script>
  const tabs = document.querySelectorAll<HTMLButtonElement>('.tab');
  const panels = document.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>('.panel');
  tabs.forEach((t) => t.addEventListener('click', () => {
    tabs.forEach((x) => { x.classList.remove('active'); x.setAttribute('aria-selected', 'false'); });
    t.classList.add('active');
    t.setAttribute('aria-selected', 'true');
    panels.forEach((p) => (p.hidden = p.dataset.panel !== t.dataset.tab));
  }));
</script>
